# Fluff Date: 2026-02-28 16:10:19
<overview>
<p>The Behemoth is the largest DropShip class ever constructed, a hundred-thousand-ton Spheroid cargo hauler that dwarfs even the Mammoth class at nearly twice its tonnage. Incapable of atmospheric operations or planetary landings due to its sheer mass, the Behemoth relies on orbital cargo stations or shuttle craft to transfer goods to a planet's surface. This additional stage in loading operations increases operating costs considerably, limiting the vessel's economic appeal to most merchant lines.</p><p>Despite these limitations, the Behemoth remains indispensable for bulk cargo operations where no other vessel can match its capacity. Its twenty cargo decks can accommodate nearly eighty thousand tons of goods, making a single Behemoth transit worth dozens of trips by smaller vessels. The design has endured across centuries of service, proof of the soundness of its original engineering.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The Clan-operated Behemoth C replaces the entire energy weapon suite with Clan-grade equivalents. Each side mounts two Clan ER large lasers and four Clan ER medium lasers, while the aft arc carries two Clan ER medium lasers. These extended-range models provide significantly greater engagement distances compared to the Inner Sphere originals, though the weapons load remains otherwise identical in configuration. Slightly increased armor coverage of 211 points supplements the upgraded weaponry. The cargo capacity increases marginally to over seventy-five thousand tons thanks to weight savings from the more efficient Clan weapons technology.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>Clan-operated Behemoths have been observed in service since at least the Clan Invasion era, though whether these vessels were built by the Clans or captured from Inner Sphere operators remains a matter of debate. Their presence among Clan naval assets suggests the design's cargo capacity fills a logistical need that even Clan engineering has not surpassed with a purpose-built alternative.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Behemoth class has a complicated design history stretching back to the mid-twenty-seventh century. The Terran Hegemony originally commissioned the design alongside the smaller Mammoth class, promising the designer that both classes could be sold to foreign powers. When the prototypes entered their final development phase around 2650, the Hegemony reneged on that promise, restricting both designs to domestic use only. In 2650, two prototypes were stolen from their orbital moorings and sold to the highest bidder, raising fears that the designs could be reverse-engineered by rival states.</p><p>The theft forced the Hegemony to reconsider its stance, and it ultimately permitted the original manufacturer to sell the design abroad. Although suspicion lingered that the manufacturer had somehow been involved in the heist, nothing was ever proven. This decision to share the design with foreign powers ensured that the Behemoth would remain in production even after the original manufacturer's demise. The finalized production variant entered service in 2782, and multiple shipyards across the Inner Sphere took up manufacturing, ensuring the class survived the Succession Wars intact.</p><p>Visual evidence confirms that at least some Clan forces have operated variants of the Behemoth, though whether these vessels were built by the Clans or captured during the Clan Invasion remains uncertain. Clan-operated examples have reportedly featured upgraded energy weapon suites, though detailed configuration data remains scarce.</p>
</history>

